  "body": "_Geth user experimenting with Erigon._\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `2.30.0-dev-d08c0521`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04.4 LTS\r\n\r\nCommit hash : 35f493c5d021965f994bee615d441b2b35811f8f\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nIndependent rpcdaemon configured with `--http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool` have access to `net`.\r\n`X-ERIGON-HEALTHCHECK min_peer_count` replay positive or negative results accordingly. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nSeparated RPC daemon (`rpcdaemon`) configured with:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n--http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, after health check trough rpcdaemon _( custom port 2222 )_:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -k -s --location --request GET 'http://127.0.0.1:2222/health' \\\r\n  --header 'X-ERIGON-HEALTHCHECK: min_peer_count10'\r\n  ```\r\nGetting this error:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"min_peer_count\": \"ERROR: connection closed before server preface received\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nGetting same error from erigon process on port `8545` until this changes implemented _(default: \"eth,erigon,engine\")_:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nerigon --http.api=eth,erigon,engine,net\r\n```\r\n\r\nFrom this point erigon process replay as expected with:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"min_peer_count\": \"HEALTHY\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nRPC daemon still trow error even after.\r\n\r\nIt sims rpcdaemon configured with `net` have no access to peers count or net functionality in general.\r\n\r\nShould `--http.api=` be configured identical on both erigon and rpcdaemon, how it works exactly ?\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behavior\r\n\r\nRun rpcdaemon with `--http.api=eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool`, do healthcheck:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -s --location --request GET 'http://127.0.0.1:3000/health' \\\r\n  --header 'X-ERIGON-HEALTHCHECK: min_peer_count10'\r\n  ```\r\n```json\r\n\"min_peer_count\": \"ERROR: connection closed before server preface received\"\r\n```\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nnothing\r\n",
